Material examined earlier
. See list of material in 
Sinev (2001)
. Morphology of studied specimens (see 
Fig. 9
) agrees with the earlier descriptions of the species (
Frey 1988
; 
Alonso 1996
; 
Sinev, 2001
; 
Van Damme & Dumont 2008a
; 
Hudec, 2010
). Additional seta near scraper 1 of limb II (
Fig. 9C
) was found in all studied populations, and lateral aestetascs on male antennule (
Fig. 9E
) was found in all studied populations with males present.
